All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AddPart
The AddPart class is responsible for managing the user interface and functionality of the Add Part screen in the inventory management system.
AddProduct
The AddProduct class is responsible for managing the user interface and functionality of the Add Product screen in the inventory management system.
InHouse
The InHouse class represents a Part object that is manufactured in-house.
Inventory
The Inventory class represents a collection of Parts and Products.
InventoryApplication
FUTURE ENHANCEMENT The main class of the Inventory Management System application, responsible for launching the GUI and initializing the inventory.
InventoryApplication.ScreenType
A ScreenType enumeration is made for each scene that is made available in this program.
MainScreen
The MainScreen class is responsible for managing the user interface and functionality of the main (landing) screen in the inventory management system.
ModifyPart
The ModifyPart class is responsible for managing the user interface and functionality of the Modify Part screen in the inventory management system.
ModifyProduct
The ModifyProduct class is responsible for managing the user interface and functionality of the Modify Product screen in the inventory management system.
Outsourced
The Outsourced class represents a Part object that was sourced from an outside entity.
Part
The Part class represents an item that can be associated with various Products.
Product
Represents a product in the inventory management system.
